The paper discusses the evolution of visual object recognition architectures based on Convolutional Neural Networks & Convolutional Deep Belief Networks paradigms, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed architecture is a deep learning architecture, which involves supervised and unsupervised learning approaches, and is inspired by the divide and conquer principle, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the training of leaf level models, which involves the use of natural language processing techniques, which falls under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
